Metrics about data not processed or stored when you exceed your SignalFx subscription limits for a sustained period of time.

Data Ingest per Token


Metrics about the volume and nature of data that SignalFx is processing and storing for you, such as the number of datapoints received per minute, tracked per token.

chart.programText:
A = data('sf.org.numInactiveTimeSeries', extrapolation='last_value').publish(label='A')
B = data('sf.org.numInactiveTimeSeries', extrapolation='last_value').timeshift('1w').publish(label='B', enable=False)
C = (100*(A-B)/B).publish(label='C')

chart.programText:
A = data('sf.org.numThrottledMetricTimeSeriesCreateCalls', extrapolation='zero').sum().scale(60).publish(label='A', enable=False)
B = data('sf.org.numLimitedMetricTimeSeriesCreateCalls', extrapolation='zero').sum().scale(60).publish(label='B', enable=False)
C = data('sf.org.numPropertyLimitedMetricTimeSeriesCreateCalls', extrapolation='zero').sum().scale(60).publish(label='C', enable=False)
D = (A+B+C).publish(label='D')

options.markdown:
Engagement Summary


Metrics about your users and the content they have created in SignalFx.

Metric(s): sf.org.numEventsDroppedThrottle Number of [events](https://docs.signalfx.com/en/latest/concepts/data-model.html#events-and-event-time-series) sent to SignalFx for your organization that were not processed or stored.

Metric(s): sf.org.numDatapointsDroppedThrottle, sf.org.numDatapointsDroppedExceededQuota Number of [datapoints](https://docs.signalfx.com/en/latest/concepts/data-model.html#datapoints) sent to SignalFx for your organization that were not processed or stored. For more information, see [DPM Limits - FAQ](https://docs.signalfx.com/en/latest/_sidebars-and-includes/dpm-faq.html).

chart.name: Dashboards and Charts
chart.programText:
A = data('sf.org.num.page', extrapolation='last_value').mean(over='1h').publish(label='A')
B = data('sf.org.num.dashboard', extrapolation='last_value').mean(over='1h').publish(label='B')
C = data('sf.org.num.chart', extrapolation='last_value').mean(over='1h').publish(label='C')
